  "issue_title": "Evaluate raising genie-ai-runtime context default to 8192",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nJetson testing shows `genie-ai-runtime` can load a larger INT8-KV context when it starts before memory-heavy services. The current repo default is safer, but may be lower than needed for normal GeniePod runtime use.\n\n## Jetson observations\n\nTest setup:\n\n- Stopped `genie-core`, `genie-health`, `genie-api`, `genie-whisper*`, `homeassistant`, `genie-ai-runtime*`\n- Ran `sync; echo 3 > /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches`\n- Started `genie-ai-runtime` with `--int8-kv` and systemd drop-in `GENIEPOD_AI_RUNTIME_CONTEXT=<CTX>`\n\nResults:\n\n- `CTX=4096`\n  - Loaded actual `Context: 4096 tokens`\n  - KV cache: `288 MB`\n  - Runtime budget free: `1903 MB`\n  - Direct runtime chat completed in `0.722s`\n\n- `CTX=6144`\n  - Loaded actual `Context: 6144 tokens`\n  - KV cache: `432 MB`\n  - Runtime budget free: `992 MB`\n\n- `CTX=8192`\n  - Loaded actual `Context: 8192 tokens`\n  - KV cache: `576 MB`\n  - Runtime budget free: `1616 MB`\n  - Direct runtime chat completed in `0.725s`\n\nImportant contrast:\n\n- When `CTX=4096` was tested while the full stack had already been running, runtime only loaded `Context: 1735 tokens (user-requested, memory cap 1735)`.\n- This means startup order and resident service memory materially affect the runtime's loaded context.\n\n## Proposed work\n\nEvaluate whether GeniePod should default `GENIEPOD_AI_RUNTIME_CONTEXT` to `8192` for the Jetson Orin Nano 8 GB profile, while ensuring `genie-ai-runtime` starts early enough to claim the intended KV cache before memory-heavy services load.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Decide whether the default should remain `2048`, move to `4096`, or move to `8192`.\n- If increasing the default, verify full-stack startup still keeps:\n  - `genie-ai-runtime` healthy\n  - `genie-core` healthy\n  - dashboard chat working through `:3000`\n  - voice/whisper services able to start after runtime\n- Document the reason for the chosen default in the systemd unit or setup notes.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis does not replace prompt compaction for `genie-ai-runtime`. Larger context prevents rejection/capping, but full system/tool prompts can still create slow prefill and poor web UI latency.\n",
